Place a #baking sheet{} on top rack and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry all produce. Dice @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. Trim and quarter @Zucchini{1} lengthwise; cut crosswise into 2-inch pieces.

Place potatoes in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. Reserve ½ cup potato cooking liquid, then drain and return potatoes to #pot. Mash with @Sour Cream{2%tablespoon} and @Butter{1%tablespoon} until smooth, adding splashes of reserved potato cooking liquid as needed. Keep covered off heat.

While potatoes cook, toss zucchini in a #large bowl{} with a large drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{4%teaspoon}, @Salt, @Pepper, and @Italian Seasoning{1%teaspoon}. Carefully spread out on preheated baking sheet. Roast on top rack until golden brown and slightly crispy, ~{14-16%minutes}.

Pat @Pork Cutlets{12%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with salt and pepper. Heat a large drizzle of oil in a #large nonstick pan{} over mediumhigh heat. Add pork and cook until golden brown and cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes} per side. (For 4 servings, you may need to cook in batches.) Transfer to a #plate. Wipe out pan.

Add ¼ cup water, @Chicken Stock Concentrate{1}, and any resting juices from pork to same pan over medium heat. Stir in @Fig Jam{2%tablespoon} and @Balsamic Vinegar{5%teaspoon}. Bring to a simmer and cook until slightly thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Turn off heat and stir in @Butter{1%tablespoon}. Season with salt and pepper.

Stir a splash more reserved potato cooking liquid into potatoes to rewarm, if necessary. Divide potatoes, zucchini, and pork between plates. Spoon sauce over pork and serve.

> This fun and fruity recipe will get your tastebuds dancing! Perfect for a square meal that totally rocks.